# No New Legacy Feature Flag Usage

The legacy `FeatureToggles` interface is deprecated. **Do not introduce new calls** to any of the following:

## Blocked Go Patterns

```go
// ❌ Do not use — deprecated
features.IsEnabled(ctx, featuremgmt.FlagXxx)
features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagXxx)
featuremgmt.AnyEnabled(features, ...)
```

Use OpenFeature instead:

```go
// ✅ Use this
client := openfeature.NewDefaultClient()
enabled, _ := client.BooleanValue(ctx, featuremgmt.FlagXxx, false, openfeature.TransactionContext(ctx))
```

## Blocked TypeScript Patterns

```typescript
// ❌ Do not use — deprecated
import { config } from '@grafana/runtime';
if (config.featureToggles.myFeature) { ... }
```

Use OpenFeature instead:

```typescript
// ✅ React component
import { useBooleanFlagValue } from '@openfeature/react-sdk';
const enabled = useBooleanFlagValue('myFeature', false);

// ✅ Non-React
import { getFeatureFlagClient } from '@grafana/runtime/internal';
const enabled = getFeatureFlagClient().getBooleanValue('myFeature', false);
```

## When Reviewing Code

If you see new `IsEnabled`, `IsEnabledGlobally`, `AnyEnabled`, or `config.featureToggles` usage being added, flag it and suggest the OpenFeature equivalent. Existing legacy usage is being migrated incrementally — this rule applies only to **new** code.
